index_struct.text: This __init__.py file is used to initialize the token_predictor module, which is used to predict the next token in a sequence of tokens. It contains functions, classes, and variables that are used to create a token predictor model using algorithms such as recurrent neural networks and long short-term memory (LSTM). The model is able to process data and make predictions based on the relationships between the functions, classes, and variables. The code file provides the necessary components to create a token predictor model, train it, and make predictions. The algorithms used to create the model are recurrent neural networks and LSTM, and the data structures used are functions, classes, and variables. The relationships between the functions, classes, and variables are used to process data and make predictions. The purpose of the code is to provide the necessary components to create a token predictor model and make predictions.
